Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}(finely diced). Halve @Lime{1}(halved). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Core, deseed, and cut @Poblano Pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and cut into ½-inch pieces). Drain @Black Beans{13.4%oz} over a #small bowl{}, reserving liquid.

In a separate small bowl, combine tomato, a big squeeze of lime juice, and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tsp}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and poblano; cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp} and half the beans (you'll use the rest in the next step). Cook, stirring, until fragrant and warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining beans and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add ¼ cup reserved bean liquid (½ cup for 4 servings). Simmer until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

Remove pot from heat; mash beans with a #potato masher{} until mostly smooth. Season with plenty of salt and pepper.

Spread @Flour Tortillas{6} with mashed beans. Place a small amount of filling on one half of each tortilla, then sprinkle with @Pepper Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}(diced).

Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create flautas. Place, seam sides down, on a #plate{}.

Wash out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add flautas, seam sides down. Cook, carefully turning so they stay intact, until golden brown and crispy, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

> Work in batches if necessary and watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide flautas between plates and top with @Guacamole{4%tbsp}, tomato, and @Sour Cream{4%tbsp}. (Alternatively, serve with toppings on the side for dipping.) Cut remaining lime half into wedges and serve on the side.